********************** Steps to run the program from the command line **********************

1. Open window's command prompt (cmd).

2. Enter "cd" + the path to the sources root folder.
   ---> Ex: "C:\Users\patri\Desktop\Java_it\SPRINT1\TASCA_5\N1\src"

2. Compile the files. Enter javac + package's name/className.java.
   ---> Ex: "<C:\Users\patri\Desktop\Java_it\SPRINT1\TASCA_5\N1\src>javac Ex1/Parking.java"

3. Execute the app. Enter java + package's name/className + package's name.
   ---> Ex: "<C:\Users\patri\Desktop\Java_it\SPRINT1\TASCA_5\N1\src>java Ex1/Parking Ex1"

4. The program will ask for a path to a directory.
   ---> Ex: "C:\Users\patri\Desktop\Java_it\SPRINT1\TASCA_3\N1\src"

4. The program will sort alphabetically the elements inside that directory.

************** Thank you. **************